Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
**12 REASONS TO BUY**
1 .Prime corner position with easy access from all approaches
2. Huge 4,520m² site with 135m corner frontage
3. Just over two (2) years old
4. 14 secured tenancies of excellent variety from medical to 
    food
5. 1,335m² of Net Lettable Area divided from 45m²–174m²
6. 48 car parks on site plus ample on street parking
7. New building depreciation allowance
8. Opposite dual child care centres and a short walk to 
    Smithfield State High School and Holy Cross Primary School
9. High population growth suburb now approx. 65% developed
10. Located on the main thoroughfare through the estate 
      linking Trinity Park to McGregor Rd and Yorkeys Knob
11. Strong future business growth prospects as population 
      increases
12. True net income of $470,000 + GST

GENERAL CONSTRUCTION - 
The property has been constructed as a single level “L” shape facing the main road frontages of Smithfield Village Drive & O’Brien Road
+ Painted rendered external concrete block walls
+ Steel framed awnings along all street front facades
+ A mixture of polished concrete, tiles and carpeted floors to 
   shop areas
+ Painted internal plasterboard walls with grid tiled ceilings 
   throughout
+ Powder coated aluminium framed shopfronts and fixed 
   glazing
+ Colorbond roofing & gutters
+ Recessed fluorescent lighting throughout
+ Ducted air-conditioning throughout each tenancy
+ Three sets of shared male/female toilets
+ Sink units in each tenancy
+ Secured refuse area and cleaners store room
+ Bitumen car parking & landscaping to council requirements
+ Power is supplied by private meters invoiced monthly to each 
   tenant

SMITHFIELD VILLAGE CATCHMENT
There are approximately 1300 lots in The Smithfield Village Estate to be developed of which 840 are complete (65%). It is expected that the remaining 460 lots will be completed within the next 6–8 years. In addition, a further 105 lots are to be
developed starting later this year at Johanna Road/Navigator Drive which will connect directly to Smithfield Village Drive only 5–10 minutes from the village shops. The balance of Bluewater Estate and Bluewater Harbour Estate also provides a further catchment of an additional 2,500 people.
